voice_to_text: can you imagine being a history teacher today and teaching about the French Revolution and just no this was honestly my experience being a high school history teacher for the last 12 years and every year it got more and more surreal and more more difficult to keep a straight face there were so many lessons that I started to have to preface if you like I promise I haven't changed this in the 12 years I've been teaching like I promise I'm not trying to make a political point for example when I would teach about Watergate one Gen Z was like unfazed by Watergate they were like that was it was all he did broke in tried to wire tap some phones that's not that bad like they're so jaded about the state of our political system I think as they should be and then when I explained like Nixon fighting back and being like it's a witch hunt they're all out to get me like people thought like my students thought I was joking they thought I was putting stuff in to make little jabs at Trump and I was like no I genuinely just this is just what happened teaching about the revolutions went from being like oh the French Revolution is this fun silly thing that almost feels unreal to every year getting a little more and more real like every year when I would teach about the Gilded Age and like the titans of industry and we talked about Carnegie and Rockefeller and Vanderbilt all the kids would go like so like Zuckerberg and Bezos and Musk I’d be like I that's a really interesting connection

voice_to_text: funny video but not incorrect about the global implications of Project 2025 a recent article by Gillian Kane for In These Times has already outlined the ways in which Project 2025 is already being implemented around the world particularly around reproductive rights and LGBTQ rights for those who don't know Project 2025 is a wish list at over 900 pages for white nationalists and Christian fundamentalists it includes such goals as eliminating the department of education and renaming the department of health and human services the  "department of life" 🤮 🤮 🤮  just in February of this year Uganda hosted Valerie Huber she is a abstinence only Christian fundamentalist who is spearheading a really critical program that has grown out of Project 2025 the program is called Protego Health the Women's Optimal Health Framework and it is a program that has been developed in order to get countries in line with the Geneva Consensus Declaration or the GCD  now the GCD was formalized and launched in the last year of the Trump administration but its goals were to export anti LGBTQ policies and anti abortion policies around the world and Protego happens to be a tool for implementing those policies now the GCD was initially signed by 32 countries but after elections in Brazil and Colombian in the United States more left leaning leaders have withdrawn their countries from this declaration the GCD claims to do four things it has four pillars  it's improving women's health protecting human life strengthening the family  and protecting each country's national sovereignty to "support their own core values" however these pillars are a smoke screen the main goal of the GCD is to strip countries of development aid if they are providing their people with reproductive health and freedom and LGBTQ rights it is a formalized, organized, right wing takeover of reproductive health and LGBTQ rights throughout the world now the point of this article is not to make people fearful or to lose hope the point of the article is to better understand what Project 2025 is and know that it's not just going to happen on Election Day if Trump wins it's already being implemented right now and the Democratic Party has largely been feckless in opposing it they've already caved on not flying the pride flag over embassies around the world which seems meaningless on its face but is part of a much larger plan to strip queer people of their rights around the world the same goes for people's reproductive health so I guess this is my way of saying  ask your local state and federal elected representatives who may or may not be members of the Democratic Party to please do better and please do way more than they're doing now because if the stakes are as high as they say they are it's not going well
